  "ordinal": 0,
  "summary": "Main\nBy Michalis Voutsinas and Helen Vlassi\n\nCRUDE OIL/NATURAL GAS\nChina brought in 40.24 million tonnes of crude oil in September, equivalent to 9.79 million barrels per day, or circa 2.0 percent down from a year earlier. Decreasing by 0.3 percent from a month earlier, September's reading altered the upward trend of the last two months, as independent refiners curbed throughput amid thin margins and lacklustre demand. From January to September, crude imports totalled 370.41 million tonnes, down circa 4.3 percent from a year earlier.",
